	Discoveries:
		- @Observable requires macOS 14+; using ObservableObject/@Published for macOS 13 compat
		- Swift 6 strict concurrency: NetworkMonitor needs @unchecked Sendable for NWPathMonitor callbacks
		- AppDelegate needs @MainActor for Swift 6 concurrency with NSPopover/NSStatusItem
		- XcodeGen overwrites entitlements — use entitlements.properties in project.yml to define them
		- xcode-select pointing to CommandLine Tools — use DEVELOPER_DIR env var to target Xcode-beta
		- CWInterface uses rssiValue() not rssi()
		- NWPathMonitor.pathUpdateHandler fires async — must also read currentPath synchronously on start to avoid stale initial UI
		- CLLocationManager.requestWhenInUseAuthorization() may not show dialog for debug builds outside /Applications — user must grant manually in System Settings
		- CWInterface.ssid() returns nil without Location Services; channel/signal/IP still work — display "Wi-Fi Connected" as fallback

