	Discoveries:
		- NETunnelProviderManager.loadAllFromPreferences() only returns configs the calling app created — macOS sandboxes NE per-app. Third-party apps cannot discover or toggle other apps' VPNs via Network Extension.
		- scutil --nc list (SystemConfiguration) sees all system VPN profiles read-only — gives UUID, display name, status, and provider bundle ID.
		- System Settings deep-link for VPN & Filters: x-apple.systempreferences:com.apple.NetworkExtensionSettingsUI.NESettingsUIExtension
		- When filtering items by user preferences (e.g. hidden VPNs), distinguish "none exist" from "all hidden" in empty states.

