	Discoveries:
		- Carbon RegisterEventHotKey avoids Accessibility permission requirement (vs CGEvent tap)
		- Default hotkey bindings seeded on first run via HotkeyAction.defaultBindings
		- nonisolated(unsafe) static var shared needed on HotkeyManager for Carbon callback (Swift 6 strict concurrency)
		- button.imagePosition = .imageLeading required for NSStatusBarButton to show title alongside image
		- Network-change notification needs SSID tracking + 2s debounce on disconnect to avoid false fire during network switch
		- Subnet mask via getifaddrs, gateway via netstat -rn, DNS via scutil --dns — all populated in NetworkMonitor.refreshWiFiInfo()

